    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-05-31T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-05-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="833"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d833">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00/8234</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lane</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 266</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-05-31">May 31,
                            1935</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received and read with
                    interest your strictly confidential despatch No. 829 of May 14, 1935, concerning
                    the general political situation in Nicaragua, and transmitting the views of
                    various officials with whom you have recently conversed.</p>
                <p>With reference to your request for any instructions or comments which the
                    Department may wish to give you on the situation as outlined in your despatch, I
                    may state that the general attitude which you have assumed, and specifically the
                    reply which you made to the Mexican Chargé d’Affaires in your conversation with
                    him on April 29, are completely in accord with the Department’s policy.</p>
                <p>Very truly yours,</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sumner Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
